00:00:01.description: China is situated in eastern Asia , bounded by the Pacific in the east. With a landmass of 9,600,000 sq km or one-fifteenth of the world's land mass, China is the third largest country in the world, next to Canada and Russia .

00:00:14.description: Samsung, South Korean company that is one of the world's largest producers of electronic devices. Samsung specializes in the production of a wide variety of consumer and industry electronics, including appliances, digital media devices, semiconductors, memory chips, and integrated systems.
